info.title: AODocs REST API
info.description: The AODocs REST API exposes most of the features of AODocs. It can be used to implement custom applications, third-party integration, bulk tools, or just to experiment with AODocs.

tags.name: library
tags.description: Lets you list existing libraries, create new libraries, get storage account e-mail (beta version, subject to change)

parameters.name: explicitAccessOnly
parameters.description: Whether to list only libraries with explicit access (for super administrators)

parameters.name: favoritesOnly
parameters.description: Whether to list only favorite libraries of the user

parameters.name: include
parameters.description: To filter the list of fields to have in the response (everything if left empty). The possible choices are: 'NONE', 'CLASSES', 'CATEGORY_DEFINITIONS', 'VIEWS', 'FOLDER_DEFINITION', 'WORKFLOWS', 'RELATIONS', 'PERMISSIONS', 'LIBRARY_LABELS'

parameters.name: query
parameters.description:
Terms to search in the library name (will match word prefixes).
You can search for exact phrases by quoting the whole parameter (example: "exact search" => will search for the whole words 'exact search' next to each other).
You can also use the stemming operator to search for alternative forms of the search terms (example: ~"dog eat" => will also search for the dogs, eating in any order)

post.description: [Restricted] Creates a library on the domain.
Creates a library on the domain.

parameters.name: storageAdmin
parameters.description: The email address of the storage account. If empty, the default storage account will be used.

parameters.name: libraryTemplateId
parameters.description: The ID of a library template (can be empty if either source library ID or Drive folder ID is not). To create standard library types, use one of: DOCUMENT_MANAGEMENT, TEAM_FOLDER, SECURED_FOLDER (short versions are also supported: DMS, TF, SF).

parameters.name: sourceLibraryId
parameters.description: The ID of a library in the same domain to create the library from (can be empty if either template library ID or Drive folder ID is not)

parameters.name: driveFolderId
parameters.description: The ID of a Drive folder that will become the root folder of the new library (can be empty if either template library ID or source library ID is not). All files within this folder will be imported into the new library.

parameters.name: objectStorageLocation
parameters.description: Location of the bucket to store attachments, either a customer owned bucket or a AODocs owned bucket(AODOCS_MANAGED)

parameters.name: keepDocumentCreationDate
parameters.description: Whether the documents copied from template library have their creation date set based on the original document's creation date. Else it will be the library's creation date

parameters.name: documentCopyMode
parameters.description: The mode of copy of the documents when creating the library from a template library (default value: NO_VERSION) or by copy from a source library (default value: NONE). The possible values are: 'NONE' (no document is copied), 'NO_VERSION' (only the head version of the documents is copied), 'WITH_VERSION' (all versions of the documents are copied)

get.description: List and search libraries in the domain

parameters.name: query
parameters.description:
Terms to search in the library name (will match word prefixes).
You can search for exact phrases by quoting the whole parameter (example: "exact search" => will search for the whole words 'exact search' next to each other).
You can also use the stemming operator to search for alternative forms of the search terms (example: ~"dog eat" => will also search for the dogs, eating in any order)

parameters.name: useSuperAdminAccess
parameters.description: (Super-admin only) Return libraries accessible with super admin role

parameters.name: minimumCurrentUserRole
parameters.description: Return only libraries with at least this role for the current user. Only ADMIN, WRITER, READER are valid values

parameters.name: withHidden
parameters.description: Return libraries that would be hidden from the current user.

parameters.name: storageAccount
parameters.description: Return only libraries of this storage account

parameters.name: labelIds
parameters.description: Return libraries with at least one of these labels

parameters.name: appMetadataTags
parameters.description:
Return the libraries with all the provided app metadata tags.
App metadata tags can be queried at three levels with the following syntax: 'appNamespaceId', 'appNamespaceId.tagName' or 'appNamespaceId.tagName:tagValue'.
App metadata tags can be excluded by adding a '-' character before the tag name ('-appNamespaceId', '-appNamespaceId.tagName' or '-appNamespaceId.tagName:tagValue').

parameters.name: favorite
parameters.description: If true, returns only favorite libraries

parameters.name: orderBy
parameters.description:
Sort by ascending NAME, by descending LAST_ACCESSED and TASK_COUNT or with FAVORITE_FIRST.
If orderBy is provided, only up to  results can be returned (check incompleteResults in response).
If not set results will be in an arbitrary order, but will be faster and allow to list more than 10000

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of items to return(defaults to 20, max 1000)

parameters.name: requirePreciseResults
parameters.description:
Set to true if you need an exact total result count (up to 25000) and need to check that the response contains all results (slower results).
If false, will only return an estimate of the total number of results.

parameters.name: facets
parameters.description: Set to true to enable facet results on library types, storage accounts and labels (slower response)

parameters.name: include
parameters.description:
Set additional information to return (each additional include slows the response).
Available values: STATISTICS (super admin only), LABELS, IS_FAVORITE, LAST_ACCESSED, TASK_COUNT

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token for continuing a previous list request on the next page. This should be set to the value of 'nextPageToken' from the previous response.

appMetadataTags_query_parameter.name: appMetadataTags
appMetadataTags_query_parameter.description:
Return the libraries with all the provided app metadata tags.
App metadata tags can be queried at three levels with the following syntax: 'appNamespaceId', 'appNamespaceId.tagName' or 'appNamespaceId.tagName:tagValue'.
App metadata tags can be excluded by adding a '-' character before the tag name ('-appNamespaceId', '-appNamespaceId.tagName' or '-appNamespaceId.tagName:tagValue').

customScriptId_path_parameter.description: The ID of the custom script.

customUIActionId_path_parameter.name: customUIActionId
customUIActionId_path_parameter.description: The ID of the custom ui action.

explicitAccessOnly_query_parameter.name: explicitAccessOnly
explicitAccessOnly_query_parameter.description: Whether to list only libraries with explicit access (for super administrators)

facets_query_parameter.name: facets
facets_query_parameter.description: Set to true to enable facet results on library types, storage accounts and labels (slower response)

flagName_path_parameter.name: flagName
flagName_path_parameter.description: The name of the configuration flag

inboundEmailId_path_parameter.name: inboundEmailId
inboundEmailId_path_parameter.description: The ID of the inbound email

include_query_parameter.name: include
include_query_parameter.description: To filter the list of fields to have in the response (everything if left empty). The possible choices are: 'NONE', 'CLASSES', 'CATEGORY_DEFINITIONS', 'VIEWS', 'FOLDER_DEFINITION', 'WORKFLOWS', 'RELATIONS', 'PERMISSIONS', 'LIBRARY_LABELS'

labelIds_query_parameter.name: labelIds
labelIds_query_parameter.description: Return libraries with at least one of these labels

limit_query_parameter.name: limit
limit_query_parameter.description: The maximum number of items to return(defaults to 20, max 1000)

minimumCurrentUserRole_query_parameter.name: minimumCurrentUserRole
minimumCurrentUserRole_query_parameter.description: Return only libraries with at least this role for the current user. Only ADMIN, WRITER, READER are valid values

pageToken_query_parameter.name: pageToken
pageToken_query_parameter.description: The token for continuing a previous list request on the next page. This should be set to the value of 'nextPageToken' from the previous response.

query_query_parameter.name: query
query_query_parameter.description:
Terms to search in the library name (will match word prefixes).
You can search for exact phrases by quoting the whole parameter (example: "exact search" => will search for the whole words 'exact search' next to each other).
You can also use the stemming operator to search for alternative forms of the search terms (example: ~"dog eat" => will also search for the dogs, eating in any order)

requirePreciseResults_query_parameter.name: requirePreciseResults
requirePreciseResults_query_parameter.description:
Set to true if you need an exact total result count (up to 25000) and need to check that the response contains all results (slower results).
If false, will only return an estimate of the total number of results.

storageAccount_query_parameter.name: storageAccount
storageAccount_query_parameter.description: Return only libraries of this storage account

useSuperAdminAccess_query_parameter.name: useSuperAdminAccess
useSuperAdminAccess_query_parameter.description: (Super-admin only) Return libraries accessible with super admin role

withHidden_query_parameter.name: withHidden
withHidden_query_parameter.description: Return libraries that would be hidden from the current user.

workflowEmailId_path_parameter.name: workflowEmailId
workflowEmailId_path_parameter.description: The ID of the workflow email
